textBeforeTable: Download smcroute libc6.1-udeb also a virtual package provided by Embedded GNU C Library: Shared libraries libc6.1 (>= 2.7) [ia64] dep: libc6-udeb also a virtual package provided by Embedded GNU C Library: Shared libraries libc6 (>= 2.7) [not ia64] dep: enhances suggests recommends depends Other Packages Related to smcroute Tags: System Administration: Configuration Tool, Implemented in: C, User Interface: Daemon, Networking: Routing, Role: Program, Purpose: Configuration, Routing SMCRoute is a command line tool to manipulate the multicast routes of the Linux kernel. It can be used as an alternative to dynamic multicast routers like pimd or xorp in situations where static multicast routes should be maintained and/or no proper IGMP signaling exists. static multicast router daemon ahcpd groovy2 tclex tcl-tclex netscript-2.4 nzbget openbgpd ruby-rack-mount golang-mux-dev ipip pimd
